-- China's SAIC Motor Group sees double-digit domestic auto growth
-- 
-- Mon Apr 18, 2011 11:33pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/04/19/us-autoshow-saic-group-idUSTRE73I0JW20110419

 

 SHANGHAI  (Reuters) - China's SAIC Motor Group expects China's auto market to post double-digit growth over the next five years, the group's vice-chairman Cheng Hong said on Tuesday. 

 Cheng, speaking to reporters at the sidelines of the Shanghai Autoshow, also said he expects China's subsidies for electric cars to remain in place for years. SAIC Group is the parent company of SAIC Motor Corp ( 600104.SS ). (Reporting by Lin Qi and  Fayen Wong ; Editing by Jacqueline Wong)